<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-25T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-25T23:00:00-05:00" n="268" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">883.24/21: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-25T23:00:00-05:00">October 25, 1941—11
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>604. Your 1591 of October 15, 3 p.m. Hopkins has advised as follows:
                                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“With reference to giving aid to Egypt under Lend-Lease, it
                                        is not believed that any commitment should be undertaken at
                                        this time. The situation is complex and the attitude of the
                                        British will have to be ascertained. Furthermore, all
                                        available shipping and supplies are badly needed by the
                                        British, the Russians and the Chinese.”</p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>